<item>
            <title>[TIKA-3589] Two trivial bugs in tika-app&apos;s commandline interpretation for tika-batch</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-3589</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In a private message &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kkrugler&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kkrugler&quot;&gt;kkrugler&lt;/a&gt; pointed out that log4j2 was not being correctly configured in tika-app when running in batch mode:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt; INFO  [Thread-1] 13:23:32,119 org.apache.tika.batch.BatchProcessDriverCLI BatchProcess: ERROR StatusLogger Reconfiguration failed: No configuration found for &apos;4b85612c&apos; at &apos;null&apos; in &apos;null&apos;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Separately, I noticed that &lt;tt&gt;--config=some-tika-config.xml&lt;/tt&gt; was breaking the commandline when running tika-app in batch mode.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
